message.content:
Some common misconceptions about AI include:

1. AI is infallible: People often believe that AI can never make mistakes, but this is incorrect. As intelligent as AIs might be, they are still created by humans and depend on human-made algorithms to function.

2. All automation involves AI: While AI can facilitate automation, not all automated processes involve AI. Some merely follow preprogrammed rules or rely on basic computing algorithms rather than employing artificial intelligence.

3. Job losses due solely to AI: Another misconception surrounding artificial intelligence states it will lead to massive job loss across various sectors. However, the truth is more complex - while some jobs may become obsolete; others will evolve under the influence of technology.
